    <div class="gk-tip">
      <strong>Original vs Current:</strong> The Constitution had <strong>8 Schedules</strong> at commencement (1950). Four more were added by amendments — 9th (1951), 10th (1985), 11th (1992), 12th (1992). The Constitution now has <strong>12 Schedules</strong>. UPSC frequently tests which schedule was added by which amendment.
    </div>

